**Episode 1.6 Script Expansion: The DOGE Diversion**  
SCENE START  
[INT. TESLA BOARDROOM - PALO ALTO - DAY (FEBRUARY 2025)]  
The room is silent. Outside the glass walls, a group of protesters holds signs: "DOGE = DEATH TO TESLA" and "BUILD CARS, NOT BUREAUCRACY."  
ROBYN DENHOLM (61), Chair of the Board, sits at the head of the table. ELON MUSK (53) is on a monitor via video link. He is in a cramped, wood-paneled office in D.C. A "DOGE" logo is visible on a sticker on his laptop.  
ROBYN  
(Measured)  
Elon, we need to talk about the 'Chainsaw.'  
ELON  
(Eyes scanning a second screen, distracted)  
The federal budget is a dumpster fire, Robyn. If we don't cut two trillion, this country goes bankrupt. I’m applying the First Principles of physics to the U.S. government. It’s the same thing we did at the Fremont tent.  
ROBYN  
It’s not the same thing. In Fremont, you were building cars. In D.C., you’re cutting the budgets of the people who buy them. Sales in Germany are down 48%. Our pure EV lead just evaporated to BYD. The 'brand' isn't a tech shield anymore; it’s a target.  
ELON  
(Snaps his focus to the camera)  
BYD is a volume play. Tesla is an AI and Robotics company. If I fix the regulatory environment in D.C., FSD goes global overnight. That’s worth ten BYDs.  
[CUT TO: MONTAGE - THE DOGE ERA (JANUARY - MAY 2025)]  
 * VISUAL: Musk at a podium at CPAC 2025, literally holding a chainsaw. The crowd goes wild.  
 * NARRATOR (V.O.): On January 20, 2025, the Department of Government Efficiency—DOGE—was born. It wasn't an official agency, but a "Special Advisor" role that gave Musk a skeleton key to the federal infrastructure.  
 * VISUAL: Grainy footage of a Tesla Model Y with "DOGE" decals being vandalized in a San Francisco parking lot.  
 * NARRATOR (V.O.): But for the first time, the "Musk Factor" became a mathematical liability. For every dollar Musk promised to save the taxpayer, Tesla was losing market cap.  
[INT. CNBC STUDIO - DAY]  
REPORTER  
(To camera)  
Tesla's Q1 2025 numbers are in, and they are grim. A 71% plunge in profits. Revenue down to $19.3 billion. Investors are asking: Is the CEO of Tesla actually the CEO of the United States?  
[INT. TESLA EARNINGS CALL - AUDIO ONLY (APRIL 2025)]  
ANALYST (V.O.)  
Elon, we're seeing a 'Code Red' on brand sentiment. Progressive buyers—your core demographic—are walking away. When does the DOGE work end?  
ELON (V.O.)  
(Voice tired)  
The financial house is mostly in order. I’ll be scaling back to one or two days a week in D.C. starting in May. Tesla is my primary focus.  
[EXT. THE SOUTH LAWN - WASHINGTON D.C. - MAY 30, 2025]  
Musk is walking toward a waiting helicopter. He looks older. He has spent 130 days as a "Special Government Employee."  
NARRATOR (V.O.)  
The DOGE experiment ended not with a bang, but a quiet exit. Musk retreated to Austin and Fremont to find a company in crisis. He had tried to "delete" the government, but he nearly deleted the brand that made him.  
[CLOSE UP: ELON MUSK]  
He looks back at the White House, then steps into the chopper. The door shuts.  
ELON (V.O. - Interview)  
(Reflective)  
Was it worth it? We stopped some funding that made no sense. But... I think instead of doing DOGE, I should have just worked on my companies. They wouldn't have been burning the cars.  
SCENE END  

